TY  - JOUR
AU  - Ghysels, Eric
AU  - Horan, Casidhe
AU  - Moench, Emanuel
T1  - Forecasting through the Rearview Mirror: Data Revisions and Bond Return Predictability
PY  - 2018
Y1  - 2018/02/01
DO  - 10.1093/rfs/hhx098
JO  - The Review of Financial Studies
JA  - Rev Financ Stud
VL  - 31
IS  - 2
SP  - 678
EP  - 714
SN  - 0893-9454
AB  - A previous literature has documented that bond returns are predicted by macroeconomic information not contained in yields contemporaneously. That literature has mostly relied on final revised, rather than real time macroeconomic data. We show that the use of real time data substantially reduces the predictive power of macro variables for future bond returns as well as the implied countercyclicality of term premiums. We discuss potential interpretations of our results.Received January 26, 2014; editorial decision June 16, 2017 by Editor Geert Bekaert.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rfs/hhx098
ER  - 



