TY  - JOUR
AU  - Chaudhuri, Ranadeb
AU  - Ivković, Zoran
AU  - Trzcinka, Charles
T1  - Cross-Subsidization in Institutional Asset Management Firms
PY  - 2018
Y1  - 2018/02/01
DO  - 10.1093/rfs/hhx075
JO  - The Review of Financial Studies
JA  - Rev Financ Stud
VL  - 31
IS  - 2
SP  - 638
EP  - 677
SN  - 0893-9454
AB  - We study cross-subsidization among U.S. equity products managed by institutional asset management firms. We find returns-based evidence consistent with both cross-subsidization receipt by strong recent performers that are relatively small in their firms and provision by products that are relatively large in their firms. Tax-exempt investors and taxable investors do not have a clear ranking by expertise, but tax-exempt investors’ agency issues are more complex. Accordingly, taxable clients have more flow-performance nonlinearity and receive more (and provide less) cross-subsidization. Taxable investor flows appear more discerning, but only under the circumstances conducive to cross-subsidization, suggesting that “more discerning” likely means “more cross-subsidized.”Received May 11, 2015; editorial decision April 22, 2017 by Editor Andrew Karolyi.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rfs/hhx075
ER  - 



