TY  - JOUR
AU  - Christoffersen, Peter
AU  - Fournier, Mathieu
AU  - Jacobs, Kris
T1  - The Factor Structure in Equity Options
PY  - 2018
Y1  - 2018/02/01
DO  - 10.1093/rfs/hhx089
JO  - The Review of Financial Studies
JA  - Rev Financ Stud
VL  - 31
IS  - 2
SP  - 595
EP  - 637
SN  - 0893-9454
AB  - Equity options display a strong factor structure. The first principal components of the equity volatility levels, skews, and term structures explain a substantial fraction of the cross-sectional variation. Furthermore, these principal components are highly correlated with the S&amp;P 500 index option volatility, skew, and term structure, respectively. We develop an equity option valuation model that captures this factor structure. The model predicts that firms with higher market betas have higher implied volatilities, steeper moneyness slopes, and a term structure that covaries more with the market. The model provides a good fit, and the equity option data support the model’s cross-sectional implications.Received December 20, 2013; editorial decision April 15, 2017 by Editor Leonid Kogan.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rfs/hhx089
ER  - 



